UBS Hires Chou, Kwo for Asia-Pacific Wealth Unit, Document Shows

-- B y   S t e p h a n i e   T o n g
-- 
2011-12-05T06:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-05/ubs-hires-chou-kwo-for-asia-pacific-wealth-unit-document-shows.html
UBS AG (UBSN) ’s wealth management unit hired
 Morgan Stanley (MS) ’s Valerie Chou and Linda Kwo from BNP Paribas SA
in  Hong Kong , according to an internal memo obtained by
Bloomberg News.  Chou joined as head of client coverage for the global
family office business in Hong Kong effective today, and will
report to Amy Lo, head of the Asia-Pacific ultra high net worth
business, according to the document, the contents of which were
confirmed by Fiona Chan, a Hong Kong-based spokeswoman for UBS.  Chou had previously been with Morgan Stanley Private Wealth
Management for 15 years, UBS said. She and Kwo are among the
more than 450 people hired by the Zurich-based bank’s wealth
management unit across the Asia-Pacific region this year.  Kwo joined UBS on Dec. 1 as a country team head in Hong
Kong, according to the memo. Kwo, who was most recently a
managing director at  BNP Paribas (BNP)  Wealth Management, will report
to Francis Liu, regional market manager for Hong Kong at UBS
Wealth Management, the document said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephanie Tong in Hong Kong at 
 stong17@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
